Italy's size of public debt increased to record levels
The size of Italy’s public debt in June 2016 exceeded 2.245 trillion euros.
The central bank of the country said that this amount is a historic maximum, RIA Novosti reports.
The previous negative record was set in May of this year.
Then the size of the national debt reached 2.228 trillion euros.
It is noted that for the first half of the year, the debt burden of Italy increased by 77.2 billion euros.
Earlier it was reported that at the end of 2015, the national debt of Italy was 132.7% of the country's GDP.
Meanwhile, Italian Minister of Economy and Finance Pierre Carlo Padoan predicted a decline in this indicator in 2016 to 130.9%, and in 2018 to 123.4% of GDP.
Payments from the airport received 141 victims of the terrorist attack in Domodedovo.
141 people received charitable payments from the Aviation Fund, which was created by the leadership of the Domodedovo airport to help the victims of the terrorist attack in 2011, Interfax reports.
According to the press secretary of the airport, Alexander Vlasov, two more applications are now under consideration.
"From the fund, charitable payments to the victims of the 2011 terrorist attack continue and comprehensive assistance is provided to resolve existing issues," Vlasov added, recalling that a fund's website was created specifically to facilitate interaction with the victims, containing complete information on the procedure for providing charitable assistance.
In 2011, in the arrival hall of foreign airlines Domodedovo, a suicide bomber detonated an explosive device.
As a result of the attack, 37 people were killed, another 172 were injured.
Scientists have found an animal that can live 500 years
An international group of biologists has come to the conclusion that the longest-lived vertebrate animal is the Greenland polar shark, which can live for about 500 years, reports RT.
Scientists conducted a radiocarbon analysis of the lens of the eye of 28 Greenland sharks.
The largest shark, whose length exceeds five meters, can be from 272 to 512 years.
Biologists believe that a low metabolism plays an important role in the longevity of the shark, which leads to slow development.
Female Greenland sharks reach sexual maturity only by the age of 150.
Previously, it was believed that the longest possible vertebrate animals live the "neighbor" of the shark - the Greenland whale.
The oldest individual, known to scientists, was slightly older than 210 years.
