Signs of the end.
What does Russia mean out of the crisis?
Economists have seen signs of Russia’s exit from the longest recession in twenty years.
According to analysts polled by Bloomberg, the GDP of the Russian Federation demonstrates a positive dynamics - in the second quarter, GDP decreased by 0.8% in annual terms.
This figure has been the lowest since the beginning of 2015.
According to the latest data of Rosstat, the decline of the Russian economy in the second quarter slowed to 0.6%.
The stabilization of the situation was recently also stated by the Central Bank and the Ministry of Economic Development.
There is slow growth ahead.
According to CBR experts, the recession in the Russian economy has remained in the past.
“The index estimate of Russian GDP suggests that the recession is left behind, and ahead – slow economic growth”, – stated in the bulletin of the Bank of Russia “What trends say”.
Modular GDP estimates for the current quarter of the regulator increased to 0.4%, the estimate for the fourth quarter is 0.5%.
According to the representative of the Ministry of Economic Development, during the second quarter, the decline in GDP of the Russian Federation stopped in the second quarter, amounting to 0.2%.
In the second quarter, the seasonally cleared decline in GDP was 0.2% compared to the previous quarter.
But during the quarter, the decline stopped: in April it was 0.2%, and in May and June, the change in GDP was in the range of 0-0.15, ”the representative of the Ministry of Economic Regas told Novosti.
The slowdown in the downturn of the Russian economy over the past five quarters indicates that “the bottom has been passed.”
Among other markers indicating signs of a revival of the national economy, Bloomberg calls the growth of demand for electricity and rail transportation, the revival of business.
If we make an adjustment that the year is leap year, it is clear that the dynamics in plus 1% of electricity consumption can be half due to an additional working day.
Add to this a lower average annual temperature in the first quarter.
The next argument is the growth of freight traffic, but it is difficult to obtain accurate data, and plus or minus 0.5% of the semi-annual volume can also be explained by seasonality, ”explains Kirill Yakovenko of ALOR BROKER.
However, there are other, more obvious signs of stabilization of the Russian economy.
For example, a decrease in price pressure.
In July, the consumer price index was 7.2% compared to 15.6% in the same month last year.
Moreover, the last two weeks Rosstat fixes deflation.
Prices in Russia fell for the first time in five years.
If you look at the dynamics of the ruble exchange rate, which, although it showed strong fluctuations at the beginning of the year, at the end of August since the beginning of the year strengthened by 12%.
This is also one of the signs of recovery, which should be followed by indicators from the real sector of the economy,” Yakovenko said.
In addition, since April in Russia there has been an increase in industrial production.
In June, the figure increased by 1.7%.
The rate of decline in foreign trade turnover from -32.8% in January 2016 to -20.7% in May is slowing.
The situation in the labor market also demonstrates positive dynamics, where the unemployment rate decreased to 5.4%.
It was lower only in September 2015 (5.2%).
Despite the favorable situation in the labor market, the question of real disposable incomes of the population to leave much to be desired.
In annual terms, the figure decreases by 4.8%.
This factor can slow down the economic recovery, as household spending makes a significant contribution to GDP.
As a rule, in the structure of the economy, their share exceeds 50%.
In addition to low consumer activity, the Bank of Russia’s tough policy can also be cited as risk factors for economic growth.
The regulator keeps the rate at 10.5%, which does not have the best effect on the real sector.
The insufficient level of investment is a negative factor, which hinders the development of industrial potential.
But in general, it can be assumed that by the end of the year the pace of the fall of the Russian economy will slow down to -0.5% against -3.7% in 2015, ”says Irina Rogova, an analyst at Forex Club.
The process of naturalization of athletes, recently launched in Russian football and perfectly took root in winter sports at the Olympics in Sochi, is not so actively developed in summer sports.
If in the Olympic Games in Rio for Russia and former foreigners perform, in most cases we are talking about the natives of the countries - the former republics of the Soviet Union.
But in Rio de Janeiro, we can observe the reverse process - a fairly large number of Russians act under the flags of other states.
In each case, the history of the change of citizenship is different.
Someone's parents took to another country as a child, leaving no choice.
Someone could not stand the competition for a place in the Russian national team.
And someone considered that abroad will create the best conditions for development in sports.
"AiF.ru" found at least 16 athletes who decided to change their Russian citizenship.
In the German passport of a 27-year-old girl it is written that her name is Lisa Redhich.
But before, of course, she was Elizabeth.
She was born in 1988 in Omsk.
Just four years later, as soon as the Soviet Union collapsed, Lisa’s parents decided to emigrate to Germany.
The girl had no choice.
There she decided to follow in the footsteps of her older sister - to engage in athletics.
Like her sister, Lisa chose pole vault.
She will remain in Russia, it would hardly be able to "move from the throne" Elena Isinbayeva.
Unfortunately, at the Olympics in Rio Lisa will be our only countrywoman, albeit former, in the sector for pole vaulting.
Her best achievements in this sport are the bronze of the 2010 European Championship and the silver of the continental championship in 2016, which she won again in the absence of Helena Isinbayeva.
29-year-old Elena Pirozhkova was born in Novokuznetsk in 1986.
Her parents are religious propagandists of the evangelical direction.
Mostly because of their faith, they left for the United States when the girl was only three years old.
In addition to Elena, eight more children grew up in the family.
They all lived in the small town of Greenfield in Massachusetts.
Lena began to be fond of fighting in school.
Showing good results, she moved to the city of Colorado Springs, where at the US Training Center of the US struggle continued classes under the leadership of another former Russian Vladislav Izboynikov.
At the 2012 Olympics in London, Elena lost in her first fight.
But at the World Cup in the same year - a victory.
Before that, by the way, she managed to win silver at the 2010 world championship.
After that, there was bronze in 2013 and silver in 2014.
26-year-old Maria was born in the city of Yaroslavl, where she first met synchronized swimming.
But to say that it was brought up by our coaches in Russia would be wrong.
Soon the girl’s family decided to emigrate to the United States and settle in the city of Colorado.
There Maria continued her classes.
Soon she was already part of the US national team and showed excellent results at the Pan American Games.
It is clear that at a serious international level, it can not compete with Russian synchronizers, but for America its indicators are the ceiling.
The new name, which sounds strange in Russian, Kristina Shaldibina received at the age of 11 when her parents decided to continue teaching the girl rhythmic gymnastics overseas.
Until this point, the girl was engaged in her favorite sport in her native Yaroslavl.
Having emigrated to the United States, she quickly entered the youth team of this country, and later broke into the main national team.
At the Pan American Games, 19-year-old Kristen won gold and silver.
For the first positions on the world stage, she, of course, did not have to fight, but for the United States she organized a real breakthrough - she brought the star-striped team to the Olympic Games in Rio de Janeiro.
Another of our former "artist" - Jan Berezko-Marggnerder, who plays for the German national team.
Yana was born in Togliatti.
In 2008, when the girl was 13 years old, the family decided to move to Germany - there the girl had more prospects to get into the national team.
She soon represented her country at the 2012 London Olympics.
There, however, Yana was able to take only 17 place, insufficient to get into the final competitions in the personal championship.
But two years before that, she managed to win the bronze medal of the Olympic Games - youth.
Another gymnast, only this time sports - Irina Sazonov.
If the ways of emigrating the previously mentioned athletes can be called standard, then the choice of the Irina family is very unusual - Iceland.
Ira is a pupil of the Volgograd sports school.
Naturally, in Iceland, she immediately became the champion of the country.
However, Ira is still training in Russia - specially comes to his homeland, so as not to lose skill.
In Rio, she did not perform as well as she would like.
The best place is 40 in the personal all-around.
Information about the swimmer Maria Ugolkova in the Russian information space is extremely small.
For a very long time Maria lives and trains in Switzerland.
However, for a long time, she performed under the Russian flag, showing good results - there was even a country record at a distance of 200 meters butterfly.
In 2015, she received Swiss citizenship and began to act under a red and white flag.
In Rio, her best performance is 14th place in the 4×100 comprehensive relay.
To get to the games, the girl launched a crowdfunding project, thanks to which she was able to collect about 6 thousand francs, which allowed her to pay for preparations for the Olympics.
