In the same year he won the World Youth Championship.
A year later, Croutter won the gold of the Youth Olympic Games in Singapore.
In addition to high jumps, Dmitry is engaged in long jumps and triple jumping.
31-year-old Albert is another native of Khasavyurt, who, after long performances for Russia, decided to change his sports citizenship.
However, unlike Batrov, Albert chose Romania, which will represent in Rio.
In Russia, he played for the School of Higher Sports Skills of Krasnoyarsk, in 2011 even becoming the champion of the country.
28-year-old Oleg Antonov was born in Moscow in the family of a player of the USSR national volleyball team Yaroslav Antonov.
Literally a year before the birth of his son, Yaroslav was recognized as the best volleyball player of the planet.
Soon he decided to continue his career in Italy.
There the family remained for permanent residence.
In 2015, as part of the national team, he became the bronze medalist of the European Championship, held on the territory of his new homeland.
Khadzhiev was born in Chechnya in 1994 and got with his family in the midst of the war.
Ten years later, the parents decided to emigrate.
The original goal was Norway, but it was not possible to get to this northern country - it was necessary to go to France, to Nice.
There Zelimkhan continued to learn freestyle wrestling.
Soon he won the world championship among juniors, and later qualified for the Olympic Games.
In Rio, he will be the only representative of France in the wrestling tournament.
And again a freestyle wrestling, and again a former Russian.
This time we will talk about a native of North Ossetia, who emigrated to Spain - Taimuraz Frive.
At the end of December 2012, he was granted Spanish citizenship, and he is currently playing for the national team of this country.
Prior to that, however, the 30-year-old athlete managed to be noted with high results in Russia.
He became the bronze medalist of the championships of the country in 2007 and 2008.
Tired of failure to get into the national team, Taimuraz decided to change sports citizenship.
The last in our list is a Chechen boxer, born in 1995 in the capital of Dagestan, Makhachkala, - Artur Biyarslanov.
When the boy was ten years old, his parents took their family through Azerbaijan to Canada.
There, Arthur, on the advice of his older brother, began to box.
Since then, Arthur has become the champion of Canada three times, and in 2012 became the world champion among youth.
In 2015, Biyarslanov won the gold of the Pan American Games, the first for his new homeland since 1975.
The head of the presidential administration of the Russian Federation Anton Vaino.
On Friday, August 12, Vladimir Putin appointed Anton Vaino as head of the Russian presidential administration.
Previously, this position was held by Sergei Ivanov.
“The head of state by its decree appointed Anton Vaino as the Head of the presidential administration of the Russian Federation, releasing him from office,” the decree signed by Putin and published on the Kremlin website said.
Since May 2012, Vaino has been deputy head of the presidential administration of the Russian Federation.
Anton Eduardovich Vaino was born on February 17, 1972 in Tallinn.
His father is Eduard Vaino, Chairman of the Business Council of Cuba-Russia in the Chamber of Commerce and Industry of the Russian Federation and Vice President for External Relations and Interaction with Shareholders of AvtoVAZ.
Grandfather - Karl Vaino - from 1978 to 1988 the first secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Estonia.
In 1996 he graduated from the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia, the Faculty of International Relations.
From 1996 to 2001, he worked at the Russian Embassy in Japan, then at the Second Department of Asia of the Russian Foreign Ministry.
From 2002 to 2004, he held various positions in the Office of Protocol of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2004 to 2007 - Deputy Head of the Protocol and Organizational Department of the President of the Russian Federation.
From 2007 to 2007 - First Deputy Head of the Protocol of the President of the Russian Federation.
From October 2007 to April 2008 - Deputy Chief of Staff of the Government of the Russian Federation.
On April 25, 2008 he was appointed head of the protocol of the Prime Minister of the Russian Federation, Deputy Head of the Office of the Government of the Russian Federation.
Since December 27, 2011 - Minister of the Russian Federation - Head of the Office of the Government of the Russian Federation.
On May 22, 2012, he was appointed deputy head of the Presidential Administration of the Russian Federation.
He speaks English and Japanese fluently.
