We are talking about the movement "Himest" - a society associated with the famous Turkish religious figure and oppositionist Fethullah Gulen.
It is his President Erdogan who considers the organizer of the attempted military coup, which occurred on July 15.
Fethullah Gulen lives in the United States, the Turkish authorities are demanding his extradition.
According to local media, today a warrant was issued for the arrest of Hakan Shukur, the police have already conducted searches in two houses that belong to the family of the former football player.
According to the investigation, the organization of Fethullah Gulen, in addition to Hakan Shukur himself, his father entered.
However, neither the former football player nor his relatives were there.
He and his family now live in the United States.
When he was a football player, Hakan Shukur defended the colors of several Turkish clubs and played for the national team.
He spent most of his career at Galatasaray.
In the list of foreign clubs are Italian "Torino", "Inter" and "Palermo", as well as the English "Blackburn".
He hasn’t played any of them in any of the season.
Hakan Shukur still remains the most productive striker of the Turkish national team: in his asset 112 matches for the national team and 51 goals scored.
In 2013, Hakan Shukur left his deputy post because of the ongoing corruption investigation around Erdogan’s party and his inner circle.
