The Russian Copper Company (RMC) is ready to take on social responsibility and pay more attention to the environmental aspects of its business.
This is confirmed, for example, by the fact that RMK took up the modernization of one of the oldest and most environmentally “dirty” enterprises of the country – the Karabash copper smelter plant.
The Karabash copper smelter was founded by the English Joint Stock Company, led by Leslie Urquhart in 1910.
In Soviet times, it was a significant industrial enterprise for the country's economy, and it actually provided the vital activity of the whole city.
However, in the 1990-ies due to financial problems, production was stopped, which entailed serious social problems in Karabash.
In 1998, it was decided to resume the work of the Karabash copper smelter.
It was also necessary to solve one of the main problems of the Karabash plant - environmental.
By the early 2000's, Karabash was already notorious as an environmental disaster zone.
The situation at Karabashmedi began to change in 2004, after the company came under the control of the Russian Copper Company.
The company began to modernize production, which began to gradually reduce the environmental burden on the environment.
This was recently noted by the governor of the Chelyabinsk region, Boris Dubrovsky, who visited Karabashmed in the first days of July.
The head of the Southern Urals called the changes that have occurred with the enterprise since Karabashmed moved to the RMK group.
The main measure for the modernization of "Karabashmedi" in recent years was the construction of a new sulfuric acid shop, which allows to capture up to 99.9% of metallurgical gases.
According to the President of the Russian Copper Company Vsevolod Levin, the volume of investments in this project amounted to about 7 billion rubles.
The next stage of modernization of CJSC "Karabashmed" - reconstruction of the convertible rework.
The replacement of three converters, dust holders, gas tract is scheduled for the end of 2017.
The cost of the project is 2.5 billion rubles.
In addition, at the end of 2016, it is planned to launch a new industrial wastewater treatment workshop worth 1 billion rubles.
In turn, the amounts of taxes deducted to the budget of the city of Karabash will also grow.
For the entire period of the project of the Tominsky GOK project - from the beginning of construction and before commissioning of the second stage - the federal treasury will receive 8.9 billion rubles.
And after the commissioning of the GOK, the receipt of taxes to the budgets of all levels may reach 80.9 billion rubles.
For the year of production in the Varna district, 346.3 million rubles were transferred to the budgets of different levels.
And that's in the first year.
“The longer the enterprise works successfully, the amount of deductions may be greater,” added Valery Ulanovsky.
The RMC specified that in 2015 tax deductions from Mikheevsky GOK approached 1 billion rubles.
However, the participation of RMK enterprises in the life and development of their presence is not limited to tax deductions.
RMK enterprises help to repair and maintain schools, kindergartens, sports facilities, build cultural and entertainment facilities, and improve the territories.
In 2016, one of the largest social projects of the Russian Copper Company in Karabash was a major overhaul, and in fact - almost complete restructuring of the kindergarten N9 by 95 pupils.
The building, built in 1960, was in an emergency condition.
Also on the territory of the "RMK Arena" will be located a landscape park with an artificial pond, underground and above-ground parking for 600 cars, cafes and sports shops.
RMK Arena will allow to hold spectacular professional sports events of international level.
But the main task of this project is to make physical education and sports in comfortable conditions available to residents of Chelyabinsk, primarily for children.
