Owners of messengers and postal services should identify users and delete prohibited information - this is a summary of the bill developed by the Media Communication Union (ISS), which unites the largest Russian telecom operators (Vedomosti has).
Employees of three companies - members of the Union confirmed that such a project is being discussed.
In early autumn, he should be represented to the working group under the leadership of First Deputy Prime Minister Igor Shuvalov, says the interlocutor of “Vedomosti” in the ISS.
We are talking about amendments to the laws on communication and on the media.
They stipulate that any “disseating information on the Internet that provides the possibility of exchanging electronic messaging” is obliged to identify users on the basis of the information contained in the databases of telecom operators by pre-signing with them contracts.
And also “immediately block messages or publications that contain information disseminated in violation of the requirements of Russian law.”
Otherwise, operators have the right to restrict access to the service by the decision of Roskomnadzor.
