Bulgaria shows inflation for the first time in 8 months
Inflation in Bulgaria was 1% monthly in July, as shown by national statistics.
This is the highest figure in years (since June 2012) and the first above zero since October last year, when positive 0.2% were shown.
The average annual inflation measured by the CCI over the past 12 months (August 2015-July 2016) compared to the previous 12 months (August 2014-July 2015) was -0.8%.
Consumer Price Index in July 2016 compared to June 2016. was 101.0%, i.e. Monthly inflation was 1.0%.
Inflation rate since the beginning of the year (July 2016) Compared to December 2015) was -0.2%, and annual inflation in July 2016 was Compared to July 2015. was -0.2%.
In July 2016, compared to the previous month, the increase was observed in price for the following groups of consumer goods: food and non-alcoholic beverages (1.7%); transport (1.8%); recreation and culture (6.3%); restaurants and hotels (1.2%); other goods and services (0.3%).
Prices fell on clothing and footwear (2.2%); furniture, household appliances and regular maintenance (0.5%); health (0.1%).
Prices remained at the same level as in the previous month for alcoholic beverages and tobacco; housing conditions, water, electricity, gas and other fuels; communication systems; and education.
